Java Digital Clock

Description
This Java application creates a digital clock with a graphical user interface (GUI) using Swing. It displays the current time, day of the week, and date in a visually appealing layout.

Features
Time Display: Shows current time in hours, minutes, seconds, and AM/PM format.
Day Display: Displays the current day of the week (e.g., Monday, Tuesday).
Date Display: Shows the current date in the format "Month Day, Year" (e.g., June 30, 2024).
Dynamic Update: Updates the time, day, and date every second.

How to Use
Run the MyFrame class.
The digital clock interface will appear, showing the current time, day, and date.
The time, day, and date will update automatically every second.

Technologies Used
Java
Swing (for GUI)
java.text.SimpleDateFormat for date and time formatting
java.util.Calendar for getting current date and time

Contributions
Contributions to enhance the digital clock's features or fix issues are welcome. Please fork the repository and create a pull request.
